cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with biomedical named entity recognition using machine learning algorithms and neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also proposes an extension to the IOBES model, which is a sequence labeling task, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The use of Bidirectional Long Short-Term Memory (BiLSTM) network and ensemble method also suggests the paper could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with information retrieval and text mining, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) categories respectively.
